<item>
            <title>[LU-4444] conf-sanity test_69: ZFS took too long to create 100k files</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-4444</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;This issue was created by maloo for sarah &amp;lt;sarah@whamcloud.com&amp;gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This issue relates to the following test suite run: &lt;a href=&quot;http://maloo.whamcloud.com/test_sets/17ed414e-7485-11e3-8ad9-52540035b04c&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;http://maloo.whamcloud.com/test_sets/17ed414e-7485-11e3-8ad9-52540035b04c&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The sub-test test_69 failed with the following error:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;test failed to respond and timed out&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/blockquote&gt;

&lt;p&gt;cannot find error messages, looks like the test just not finished in 3600 sec&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment>client and server: lustre-master build # 1823 RHEL6 zfs</environment>
